result.execSummary:
The defendant Cory L Hembel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Cory L Hembel in court. Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews previous activity, questions whether new offer has been made. State advises of new offer. Defendant makes statement. Court imposes sentence.

Defendant Cory L Hembel in court. Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews previous activity, has discussion with Defendant regarding resentencing. ADA Korb advises that DA Pelrine has not put offer in case regarding straight jail sentence, assumes it will be more than the 30 days time recommended as condition of probation. Court advises Defendant that State is not bound by 30 days previously offered. Defendant questions whether he can talk with DA about what new offer will be. Court questions Defendant on continued waiver of right to counsel, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver. Defendant to make appointment with DA.  Hearing scheduled for November 23, 2015 at 10:00 am.
from Defendant re: probation. Per Court, put on for hearing "Def's Request to Self-Revoke".

Defendant Cory L Hembel in court.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews previous activity, questions Defendant on progress with DA. Defendant advises it went good. State advises that offer was made, does not know Defendant's intentions. Defendant advises that he can't afford payments, advises of expenses. State advises that offer will not change. Defendant wants to accept offer. Court reviews charges, max. penalties, elements. Defendant enters no contest plea to Count 1. Court questions Defendant on rights, finds plea made freely and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds Defendant guilty of Count 1. Count 2 is dismissed but read in for sentencing. State makes sentencing recommendations. Bond no longer in effect.
No contact direct or indirect with Brick Lot Bar. Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.
